decision_conditions:
No development shall take place until a Basement Method Statement and Flood Risk Assessment have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. This statement shall include details regarding: 

Detailed site specific analysis of hydrological and geotechnical local ground conditions; 

a.	Analysis of how the excavation of the basement may impact on the water table and any subterranean water flow, and whether perched water is present; 
b.	Details of how flood risk, including risk from groundwater and surface water flooding has been addressed in the design, including details of any proposed mitigation measures for this development and elsewhere; 
c.	Details of measures proposed to mitigate any risks in relation to land instability; 
d.	Demonstration of how cumulative effects have been considered; 
e.	A comprehensive non- technical summary document of the assessments provided and information submitted against (a) to (e) of this condition. 

Reason: Development must not commence before this condition is discharged to avoid hazard in relation to land instability and increased flood risk caused by the basement excavation and to minimise any harmful impact to the free-flow and safety of the highway (Policy EN5 of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021)).
